fields.content:
As students themselves, the YAS team understands how difficult it may be to find one’s calling and guide oneself onto the path of post-secondary education or the work force. This is why we intend to bring wise professionals who have gone through this strenuous time and can help lead youth in discovering their life paths. We believe that although in our generation we are fortunate enough to have incredibly powerful technology that allows us to learn in the comfort of our homes, reading about a profession does not compare to personally hearing about one’s experiences, and learning about obstacles faced and how to overcome them.

In addition to aiding attendees with knowledge and experience, we intend to reward one attendee with a YAS scholarship. Although one can find their passion in life, finances can often cause this passion to be no more than a far-fetched dream. We hope to help make one deserving student’s dream a closer to reality by supporting him/her financially. Through YAS, we not only hope to enlighten students, but also show them how much can be accomplished through student initiative.

The YAS Team is thrilled to present the seven professions that will be represented at our inaugural year. We dedicate our conference to providing delegates with unparalleled professional guidance, intriguing opportunities, and a valuable learning experience.The selection was curated to cater to delegates wanting to pursue an array of professions, and to those seeking knowledge to help them decide. We’ve incorporated highly academic professions such as law and medicine, practical careers like the RCMP, and the cutting edge field that is game design. Each of our chosen professions further yields dozens of more specific jobs, some little known to those outside of that field.

If for some peculiar reason you find that none of these paths suit your taste, then the networking session is an opportunity for you to explore other options. Details of each career’s workshop, focus point, and description can be found on their respective pages. We are confident that delegates will have a rewarding experience through our conference.

We look forward to seeing you in in Vancouver this January.

Yours,

The YAS Team

The inaugural Youth Achieving Success (YAS) Conference is a full day event targeted towards high-school students to be held on Saturday, January 17, 2015. The conference is thought to be a “window into the future” for attendees, who will have the chance to learn about the following careers paths: Engineering, Game Design, Investment Banking, Law, Marketing, Medicine and RCMP. Consisting of a total of seven interactive workshops, each uniquely run by an experienced professional, students will not only learn of professions they may hold an interest in, but also develop an interest in careers they may have not considered. During these workshops, mentors will enlighten delegates of their respective career field and have the opportunity to participate in an intriguing activity based on that specific career field.

The YAS Conference will also include an interactive networking session in which students will have the opportunity to develop useful connections with prominent professionals in a variety of industries.

The networking session will be the most interactive portion of the conference where students will have the opportunity to discover themselves while speaking with numerous professionals from various industries. This will be a chance to ask any questions students may have and learn all they desire about the career paths that they are interested in. Moreover, this will be an opportune time for students to develop connections with their peers and professionals.
YAS 2015 will be held on Saturday, January 17, 2015 at a venue to be announced shortly.

The Youth Achieving Success team believes that no students should be limited to the career path that they are passionate about due to their financial standing. This is why YAS will be offering one of the delegates attending the YAS Conference  a scholarship of up to $1000, to be used at any Canadian university of their choice.

Details on how to apply for the YAS scholarship will be available at the YAS Conference itself, where applicants will be given an information package regarding the application process for the bursary. A winner will be chosen for the scholarship based on a specific criteria set by a panel of judges. This criteria will be posted on the YAS website soon, so that delegates understand what the YAS Scholarship application will require of them.

Details on how to apply for this financial aid will be available to delegates soon so check back often! If you have any more questions about the scholarship, please do not hesitate to refer to our Contact tab.

Have questions about YAS? We have the answers. The responses below deal with general questions about our organization and the conference such as what YAS is, delegate fees, the time and date for the conference, etc. In the event that you have further questions, contact any one of the executive members (see Contact Us) and we will get back to you as soon as we can. 


What is Youth Achieving Success? Youth Achieving Success (YAS) is a non-profit organization that strives to assist students on the path to post-secondary education not only by providing an extensive amount of knowledge, but also by aiding financially. In order to do so, YAS will be holding a Career Conference where students will have the opportunity to participate in numerous interactive workshops and connect with professionals of various fields.  


What is the YAS Career Conference? The YAS Career Conference is a full-day event that will bring different fields of work into one location where high school students will have the chance to work and learn in a professional environment of key note speakers, workshops, and a networking session. YAS will host members of a variety of fields of work instead of focusing on one single line of work, in order to help attendees learn and build interest in careers that they may not have considered. Students will be able to interact with their peers who are in similar situations, in addition to esteemed professionals who will be able to enlighten students about their futures. Students will also have the ability to meet with representatives from post-secondary institutions and find out what it takes to pursue a specific profession. All attendees will also have to opportunity to win the YAS scholarship of up to $1000. 


When and where will the conference be held? YAS 2015 will be held on Saturday, January 17, 2015


When can I register for the YAS Career Conference? Registration will begin in mid-October on the YAS website.


When is the registration deadline? More information about registration and its deadline will be available soon in the Registration tab, so check often! 


Is there a fee to attend YAS? Since YAS will be held at a prime location and YAS will be offering one deserving student a scholarship, the conference will require a very low fee of $20 from its attendees to cover food costs, and other expenses. 


Who is eligible to apply the scholarship? Anyone attending the YAS conference will be given the opportunity to apply for the scholarship. 


How can I apply? Further application details will be provided to delegates at the actual event, and a winner will be chosen based on specific criteria provided by a panel of professional judges. 


What kinds of career fields will be attending this event? Our executives have strived to have professionals from a variety of sought-after careers to attend the event. For more information on the specific fields, look under the Career Focuses tab.


Is there a dress code for YAS 2015?  YAS 2015 has a semi-formal dress code.

Dear Delegates, Chaperones, Teachers, and Parents,

As the Chair of Youth Achieving Success, I would like to invite and welcome you to the inaugural Youth Achieving Success (YAS) conference on Saturday, January 17th, 2015.

Founded by a group of students somewhat confused about their futures, YAS is a non-profit organization focused on creating an accessible conference for teenagers to discover a variety of careers and network with professionals. YAS’s goal is to enlighten high school students about diverse career paths and to lead the way into the sometimes intimidating “real world.” YAS strives to bring extensive knowledge about different fields of work into one conference where high school students will have the opportunity to work and learn in a professional environment of keynote speakers, workshops and an interactive networking session.

Although in our generation we are fortunate enough to have incredibly powerful technology that allows us to learn in the comfort of one’s home, reading about a profession does not compare to hearing about one’s experiences, and learning about the obstacles they faced and how to overcome them. This is why the YAS founders aspired to create an intimate conference in which personable professions would come in and share their stories, allowing for a hands-on learning experience.

We at YAS believe that through a structured yet intimate conference, attendees can not only discover numerous different careers, but perhaps also that one career that sparks their future into something much brighter. Living up to its non-profit status, YAS is offering yet another incentive to attend its incredible conference—financial support. Proceeds from YAS Conference will go towards a community scholarship (up to $1000) to which only YAS attendees may apply to.

All in all, as the Chair of Youth Achieving Success, and on behalf of the entire YAS team, I invite all youth to join us for a day of learning, stimulation, and achieving success.

We hope to see you there!

Sincerely,

Tejas Saggi | Chair | Youth Achieving Success 2015
Registration will be opening shortly, so check back often!
